<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-08T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-08T16:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/1304: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-08T17:00:00-04:00">March
                                        8, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1460. “From Stettinius for Harriman. Regarding your no. 1618, we have
                                asked Faymonville whether we should anticipate request for
                                agricultural tractors. In reply, he states that the Commissar,
                                Mikoyan, desires no agricultural tractors, although he will shortly
                                request spare parts to complete Soviet tractors, these parts being
                                similar to those used in older American types. It is our
                                understanding therefore that for this season the agricultural
                                tractor question has been closed.”</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>